ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's intensive research for credit. I get two credits for working 20 hours a week in my lab. It's great.
If you do research, do this. It will ensure that you understand your project and really motivate you to keep working on it.

Yeah take it if you are already planning on doing 20+ hours a week. All you have to do is give a presentation in lab and then write a 12-15 page summary (double spaced) at the end. Not too much extra work if you are already spending a lot of time in lab.
